keyValuePair.Value: Did you prepare for penalties?
It was such a tight game. Your team held its nerve and won on penalties. Did you actually go into today expecting it to come down to a shoot-out? Was that the plan?
We always play to win.

Of course it was close. We go into every game with the intention to win. But, against a team as good as that, you have to prepare for whatever might happen. So we were ready for penalties, that's for sure.
I thought we were exceptional.

I'm really pleased for every single one of them. They worked so hard and stayed organised all game. We kept a clean sheet and that was what got us to the shootout. Then, when it came to the pens, we were just ice-cool, weren't we? The boys deserve so much credit. Our fans can be proud of them.
To be honest, we should have had the game won.

We definitely had a plan to win the game in normal time today but the lads let themselves down a bit. We made chances but they didn't take them. We can definitely play better but maybe it was just the occasion got to us. Got to say I'm glad we know how to take pens, though!

We definitely had a plan to win the game in normal time today but the lads let themselves down a bit. We made chances but they didn't take them. We can definitely play better but maybe it was just the occasion got to us. Got to say I'm glad we know how to take pens, though!
Did you prepare for a shoot-out today?
Commiserations. Up against a very strong team, you must have known it would be a close contest. Was the possibility of a penalty shoot-out always part of your plan?
We're disappointed to lose but we'll learn from it.
We did everything we could. Of course we had a plan for how we could win the game in normal time but, once it goes to penalties, who knows what will happen? It wasn't our day.
The lads didn't deserve to lose today.
Our back line were excellent today. They kept a clean sheet against a very good team. It was thanks to them we got to a shoot-out. I'm just disappointed for them that we couldn't win it!
When it's pens, you have to be mentally strong.

Maybe the lads were scared to take too many risks. We were up against a team that's good on the break. But we can take lessons from this. If we'd been stronger mentally, in the game and during the shootout, it could have been us celebrating today.

Were you always expecting it to go to penalties?
You had to fight back after %1s scored and must have been happy to get the game to a shoot-out. Did you always think it might end up going to penalties?
We can be better than that.
We can be better than that.

My players are an honest bunch. They work hard and they do their best. We've won on pens so I can't be too critical, but they'll know from the game that they still need to improve. We should have had sewn up the game before it got to a shootout.

We saw some courage from the lads out there.

When we conceded that goal, I was worried what might happen. But the lads responded in a really good way and fought back. It was enough to get us to the shoot-out and, at that point, I knew we'd have the courage to come out on top. We couldn't let the fans down!

When we conceded that goal, I was worried what might happen. But the lads responded in a really good way and fought back. It was enough to get us to the shoot-out and, at that point, I knew we'd have the courage to come out on top. We couldn't let the fans down!
We can all enjoy that victory.
We can all enjoy that victory.

We'd planned for a win in normal time, of course. But I was happy we got our equaliser and then kept our nerve in the shoot-out. It was very tense out there but we were mentally strong. Let's enjoy it, rest, and then get ready for the next game.

Do you think the game always looked like going to penalties?
That must have been frustrating. Your team did so well to get back into it after %1s took the lead. But then you lost the shoot-out. Were you expecting such a close game?
We'll learn lessons from that defeat, I promise you.

We went into the game confident that we'd win. To concede was a blow but we fought back and got ourselves level. Maybe we should have pushed on from there to get a winner. As it is, we've missed out on pens. But the boys will learn lessons from today, I'm sure.
We win together and we lose together.
The boys showed great spirit to get us back into the game. I'm sorry for them that we couldn't win the shoot-out. But we'll stick together and move forward from this disappointment.
Couldn't we have done more in normal time?

We felt that, in a game against %1s, the opening goal was going to be very important. I was disappointed we didn't stay solid when it mattered, of course. Yes, we got an equaliser but that wasn't enough. Penalties are a lottery. Personally, I'm frustrated that it came down to a shootout in the first place.

We thought we would have enough going forwards to win us the game. Our attacking play had been excellent getting us this far in the competition. But, after going behind, we just didn't have enough and ran out of luck in the shoot-out. The boys just have to find a way to get over this disappointment now.
Losing on penalties is hard to take.

I thought we played some good football today, especially after going behind. We definitely didn't expect it to go to penalties. Of course boys will be disappointed tonight and we know the fans will be, too. But we have to learn our lessons and move on.
